def: Distinguished by opposite qualities. J. Goodwin.
In a slovenly, or hurried and imperfect, manner. [Low] Drayton.
The application of photography to the delineation of the sun,moon, and stars.
An order of extinct flying reptiles; -- called alsoPterosauria.
Capable of being understood or comprehended; as, anintelligible account or description; intelligible pronunciation,writing, etc.The intelligible forms of ancient poets. Coleridge.
An apparatus for determining the temperature of a distantpoint, as by a thermoelectric circuit or otherwise.
The filling or covering with water or other fluid; overflow;inundation; the filling anything to excess.
A curve, of the fourth degree, first made use of by the Greekgeometer, Nicomedes, who invented it for the purpose of trisecting anangle and duplicating the cube.
